From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 02:35:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] drm: panel: backport Raspberry Pi Display 2 profile

The Rockchip vendor 6.1 tree already ships the ILI9881C panel driver,
the older Raspberry Pi ATTINY regulator driver, and even Rockchip
overlays that reference the Raspberry Pi Display 2 compatibles. What it
does not ship is the glue that makes those three pieces line up.

Backport the Raspberry Pi 7-inch ILI9881C panel profile and accept the
newer ATTINY regulator compatible used by the official Display 2
overlay. This keeps the Lyra Zero W display support small and avoids
carrying a hand-written generic panel sequence in the board overlay.
---
